{
  "name": "portfoliolen",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## PortfolioLens — Qdrant Portfolio Agent\n\n### Two Operating Modes\n\n### WORKFLOW 1 — News Ingestion (Scheduled)\n\nRuns every 6 hours:\n\n1. Fetches financial news from the FastAPI endpoint\n2. Cleans and normalizes article content\n3. Gemini analyzes each article:\n\n   * importance\n   * sentiment\n   * summary\n   * mentioned tickers\n4. Generates embeddings using `gemini-embedding-001`\n5. Performs deduplication through Qdrant\n   (cosine similarity > 0.85)\n6. Upserts new articles into the `financial_news` collection\n7. Generates article drafts only for new high-importance stories\n8. Stores processed records in Supabase for historical tracking\n\n### WORKFLOW 2 — Portfolio Query API (Webhook)\n\nTriggered by frontend requests:\n\n1. Receives a portfolio request:\n   `{ \"tickers\": [\"AAPL\", \"NVDA\", \"BTC\"] }`\n2. Performs vector search in Qdrant for each ticker\n3. Merges and filters results by recency and relevance\n4. Gemini generates a personalized portfolio digest\n5. Returns structured JSON to the frontend\n\n### Setup\n\n* [ ] Google Gemini API credentials\n* [ ] Qdrant Cloud URL and API Key\n* [ ] Supabase credentials\n* [ ] Replace the ngrok URL with your own FastAPI endpoint\n\n### Technologies\n\n* Qdrant Cloud\n* Google Gemini\n* n8n\n* Supabase\n* FastAPI\n* React + Vercel\n\n### Purpose\n\nPortfolioLens demonstrates how vector search can be used for financial intelligence, relationship discovery, and portfolio monitoring beyond traditional chatbot interfaces.\n",
        "height": 700,
        "width": 760
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1040,
        208
      ],
